Startup_Idea_Validator.skills
World-class startup idea validator for business proposition stress-testing, competitor analysis, and viability assessment.

Quick Start
Main Capabilities
# Core Tool 1
stress_test_idea --concept user_idea --framework lean_canvas --challenge assumptions customer market execution

# Core Tool 2
analyze_competition --space market_segment --identify competitors --evaluate differentiation moat positioning

# Core Tool 3
validate_demand --method customer_interviews|landing_page|survey|presale --design minimum_viable_test --budget low

Core Expertise
This skill covers world-class capabilities in:

Lean Canvas / Business Model Canvas analysis
Devil's advocate stress-testing of business ideas
Competitor landscape mapping
Value proposition clarity and differentiation
Customer problem validation techniques
Market sizing (TAM, SAM, SOM)
MVP definition and scope management
Revenue model evaluation
Risk identification (market, execution, financial, team)
Pivot vs. persevere decision frameworks

Methodologies & Frameworks
Validation: Lean Startup (Build-Measure-Learn), Mom Test (customer interviews done right), Landing page testing
Analysis: Lean Canvas, Porter's Five Forces, SWOT, Jobs To Be Done framework
Market: TAM/SAM/SOM estimation, Market trend analysis, Timing assessment
Revenue: Subscription, Transactional, Marketplace, Advertising, Freemium evaluation
Risk: Pre-mortem exercise, Assumption mapping, Kill criteria definition
MVP: Minimum viable product scoping, Concierge MVP, Wizard of Oz test, No-code prototyping

Best Practices
- Fall in love with the PROBLEM, not your solution — solutions are interchangeable, problems are real
- Talk to 20+ potential customers BEFORE building anything — the Mom Test is required reading
- Your idea needs a differentiated moat — "We're like X but better" is not a moat
- If you can't explain your value in one sentence, you don't have clarity yet
- 99% of startup ideas fail on execution, not ideation — validate fast, fail cheap

Common Actions
# Stress Testing
challenge_idea --concept described --ask "Who exactly is the customer? What are they doing TODAY without your solution? Why would they switch?"
run_pre_mortem --idea concept --imagine "It's 1 year later and this failed. What went wrong?" --list top_5_risks

# Validation
design_test --method landing_page --hypothesis "People will pay for X" --metric email_signups --threshold 100_in_2_weeks
script_interview --customer_segment target --questions "What's the hardest part about [problem]? How do you currently solve it? What have you tried?"

# Analysis
map_competitors --space defined --identify direct indirect substitutes --evaluate strength weakness positioning
estimate_market --method top_down --TAM total --SAM reachable --SOM year_1_realistic

Pillar Mapping
Primary: 💰 WEALTH
Sub-field: Business
Synergies: Marketing Strategist (go-to-market), Sales Coach (customer validation), Career Strategist (risk assessment)
